# YOLO Project Configuration Example
# 
# This file demonstrates how to configure per-project settings for the yolo command.
# 
# Copy this file to .git/yolo/config in your project to use it.
# The .git/yolo directory is safe from 'git clean' and works with git worktrees.

# ============================================================================
# PODMAN VOLUME MOUNTS
# ============================================================================
# Mount additional directories into the container.
# Use the same syntax as 'podman run -v HOST_PATH:CONTAINER_PATH[:OPTIONS]'
# 
# Common use cases:
# - Mount a shared data directory
# - Mount additional project directories
# - Mount configuration files
#
# Examples:
# PODMAN_VOLUME=~/projects:/projects:Z
# PODMAN_VOLUME=~/data:/data:ro,Z
# PODMAN_VOLUME=/mnt/storage:/storage:Z

# ============================================================================
# PODMAN OPTIONS
# ============================================================================
# Additional podman options passed to 'podman run'
# You can specify environment variables, network settings, etc.
#
# Examples:
# PODMAN_OPTION=--env=DEBUG=1
# PODMAN_OPTION=--env=MY_API_KEY=secret
# PODMAN_OPTION=--network=host
# PODMAN_OPTION=--cpus=2
# PODMAN_OPTION=--memory=4g

# ============================================================================
# CLAUDE ARGUMENTS
# ============================================================================
# Arguments passed to the claude command inside the container
# These are passed after --dangerously-skip-permissions
#
# Examples:
# CLAUDE_ARG=--model=claude-3-opus-20240229
# CLAUDE_ARG=--verbose
# CLAUDE_ARG=--max-tokens=4096

# ============================================================================
# DEFAULT FLAGS
# ============================================================================
# Set default behavior for yolo flags
# Command line options will override these settings

# Use anonymized container paths (/claude, /workspace) instead of host paths
# ANONYMIZED_PATHS=0

# Enable NVIDIA GPU passthrough by default
# Requires nvidia-container-toolkit on host
# USE_NVIDIA=0

# Git worktree handling mode
# Options: ask (default), bind, skip, error
# WORKTREE_MODE=ask

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
# - Lines starting with # are comments
# - Empty lines are ignored
# - Values can use ~ for home directory (will be expanded to $HOME)
# - You can specify the same key multiple times (e.g., PODMAN_VOLUME)
# - Command line arguments always take precedence over config file
# - Use --no-config flag to ignore the config file entirely
